Day 3 Conditional Statements

This task is about using conditional statements in Python to solve simple problems.

Program 1 Even or Odd

This program takes a number as input and checks whether it is even or odd.

Expected Outcome
The program should print whether the entered number is even or odd.

Actual Outcome
The program ran successfully and displayed the correct result.

Program 2 Largest of Three Numbers

This program takes three numbers as input and compares them to find the largest number.

Expected Outcome
The program should display the largest number among the three inputs.

Actual Outcome
The program compared the values correctly and printed the largest number.

Program 3 Pass or Fail

This program takes marks as input and checks whether the student has passed or failed.

Expected Outcome
If the marks are 35 or above the result should be Pass otherwise Fail.

Actual Outcome
The program evaluated the marks correctly and displayed the appropriate result.

Final Outcome
By completing this task I was able to understand and apply conditional statements in Python to solve logical problems.